20/12/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- OSCE Chairman-in-Office and Slovenian Foreign Minister Dimitrij Rupel welcomed on Monday (19 December) Brussels' decision to grant EU candidate status to Macedonia. 
He stressed that this reflects the significant progress achieved by the country in the past four years, but noted reforms must continue in the political and economic sectors.
In other news, the Macedonian Army's First Mechanised Infantry Brigade was inaugurated at a formal ceremony in Stip on Monday. 
President Branko Crvenkovski noted that this was one of the first such units to have been transformed fully in line with NATO standards. 
(OSCE Web site, Makfax - 19/12/05)
